14/01/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- The Human Rights Union Party (HRUP), an ally of the ruling Democratic Party, said on Sunday (January 13th) it would leave the government unless a reorganization takes place.
"Changes in the government are necessary, ahead of entering the last year of the governing mandate," said HRUP head Vangjel Dule.
In other news Sunday, President Bamir Topi praised the work of the Albanian State Police at a ceremony in Tirana.
Officials marked the 95th anniversary of the police forces.
Topi thanked employees for their enormous contribution to the protection of law and order in Albania and awarded the state police with the Medal of Gratitude for achieving the standards of law and order required by the EU and NATO.
(Koha Jone, Gazeta Shqiptare, Shqip, Shekulli - 14/01/08;
Albanian President web site, Balkanweb, Top-Channel - 13/01/08)
